  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Grant Aid in Response to the Ebola Virus Disease Outbreak in the Democratic Republic of Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to support national efforts in responding to the on-going ebola epidemics (9th and 10th) in the Democratic Republic of Congo while strengthening national capacity to better prevent, detect and respond to public health emergencies in the future. The project is aligned with the National Response Plan (May 2018), World Health Organization&apos;s (WHO) Strategic Response Plan (May 2018) and the recommendations from the Joint External Evaluation (JEE) on the implementation of the International Health Regulations (IHR) conducted in March 2018. The project will focus on strengthening surveillance at point of entries and at important congregation points, cross border coordination and technical and operational support for contingency planning specifically as it relates to capacity building of International Health Regulations (2005) core capacities.</narrative>
  </description>
